[{"date":"2015-12-06T00:00:00Z","dateAdded":"2015-11-24T21:52:41Z","dateSeen":["2016-07-08T00:00:00Z"],"rating":5.0,"sourceURLs":["https://www.amazon.com/Laco-1925-861690-Classic-Stainless/dp/B009LDPTDU","http://www.amazon.com/Laco-1925-861690-Classic-Stainless/dp/B009LDPTDU"],"text":"This is a tremendous value for the watch you will receive. Most important to me is the historical significance, since this company originally manufactured a larger version of this watch (a flieger) for the German air force in WW2. From a design perspective, it is practical and is not something everyone else has on their wrist. The Miyota movement is a workhorse movement with a smooth 6bps sweep, and it looks attractive through the display back. For me, that was definitely worth paying the extra money compared with the quartz version but not worth spending the extra money for the Swiss ETA-based movement (8bps and generally considered to be higher quality than a Japanese movement). The lume is also pretty bright.For a unique, eye-catching design, automatic movement, and sapphire crystal (front and back), you would be hard-pressed to find a better watch at this price. Combine that with the history of the watch and the small, family-owned watchmaker that produces it, and it's a no-brainer.","title":"Perfect combination 3 people found this helpful. From a design perspective, it is practical and is not something everyone else has on their wrist. The Miyota movement is a workhorse movement with a smooth 6bps sweep, and it looks attractive through the display back. For me, that was definitely worth paying the extra money compared with the quartz version but not worth spending the extra money for the Swiss ETA-based movement (8bps and generally considered to be higher quality than a Japanese movement). The lume is also pretty bright.For a unique, eye-catching design, automatic movement, and sapphire crystal (front and back), you would be hard-pressed to find a better watch at this price. It feels very weak when winding and leaves the impression that the first time it gets even a glancing blow that it will snap. [{"date":"2015-04-17T00:00:00Z","dateAdded":"2015-12-01T03:20:31Z","dateSeen":["2015-11-27T00:00:00Z"],"sourceURLs":["http://www.amazon.com/Clorts-Mens-Water-Athletic-Shoes/dp/B00N8RLKVA","http://www.amazon.com/Clorts-Water-Athletic-Shoes-US9-5/dp/B00N8RLD1W","http://www.amazon.com/Clorts-Seaside-Amphibious-Athletic-Sneaker/dp/B00N8RLKVA","http://www.amazon.com/Clorts-Mens-Water-Athletic-Shoes/dp/B00N8RK39U"],"text":"I first found these shoes in a sporting store in China on a hot summer day while my feet were rotting to death in my leather shoes. Was I surprised how great they were. I could feel the air passing through them as I walked along the hot marble tiles outside. They literally saved my feet from certain death. I loved them so much that I bought two more pair of the same shoes and two pairs of the Clorts's closed toe sandals. The shoes are nice and wide for my fat feet and the insoles are really great, but can also be taken out and there is enough vertical space in the shoes to add your own, even thick insoles with the thick gel heels or big arch supports.Cons, I have to wear socks when wearing them or my feet get hot, so thin super breathable socks were my choice while in Asia. Also because there are water drain holes in the bottom of the shoes you don't want to walk through rain or any wet surface.I cannot over emphasize my love of these shoes, great quality, great materials. They're my second pair of Geox driving shoes, I recommend them to men who need a good fit, especially if your size is 12-1/2 US, which most American shoemakers do not offer. Good value.","title":"Comfortable, well-fitting shoes.","username":"William P. Stallsmith"},{"date":"2014-07-24T00:00:00Z","dateAdded":"2015-09-20T20:42:28Z","dateSeen":["2015-09-19T00:00:00Z"],"sourceURLs":["http://www.amazon.com/Geox-Fast11-Driving-Moccasin-Coffee/dp/B005BSRACC"],"text":"Love the brand and these are my 4th pair but these are so narrow!So either send back or have them stretched wider!","title":"Love the brand and these are my 4th pair but ...","username":"E D Guggenheim"},{"date":"2012-12-16T00:00:00Z","dateAdded":"2015-09-20T20:42:28Z","dateSeen":["2015-09-19T00:00:00Z"],"sourceURLs":["http://www.amazon.com/Geox-Fast11-Driving-Moccasin-Coffee/dp/B005BSRACC"],"text":"I got my first pair of these shoes about a couple of years ago. I ended up wearing them more than expected and thus had to replace them a lot sooner than what is the norm for me. The reason I wore them so much is due to the styling. In other words, they go well with a pair of jeans and even in business casual attire.Although the shoes are a bit pricey in comparison to other casual shoes on the market, the Geox has a few features which justify the cost for me. First, is the styling which - as mentioned above - allows me to wear them most anytime. Second is that they are really comfortable. The first pair I obtained were a wide size and fit quite well. For my second pair, I was not able to locate a wide size and so I opted to buy a shoe that was a half size bigger. So far, so good in this regard.The other thing about these shoes is that do a good job of repelling foot odor. Evidently this is a patented feature of Geox shoes and, I must say, that my shoes never really failed me in this regard. And, I must admit that my feet can get a bit sweaty after a day of walking around in warm tempratures.Needless to say, the fact that I bought a second pair is indication in and of itself that I am happy with the shoes. If I had a complaint, it is in the fact that these shoes are hard to find. I actually searched for quite a while to find this shoe in the right color and in a size that I felt I could live with. I hope the search will be easier when it comes time to buy the next pair.","title":"Great shoe for different situations","username":"Christopher J."},{"dateAdded":"2015-09-20T20:42:28Z","dateSeen":["2015-09-19T00:00:00Z"],"sourceURLs":["http://www.amazon.com/Geox-Fast11-Driving-Moccasin-Coffee/dp/B005BSRACC"],"text":"Very comfortable, very predictable fit. I do not wear socks, to the fact that the shoe breaths better than normal shoes is a plus . . . for everyone around me. I've probably had 6 - 8 pair of these type of Geox shoes (various colors) and they are always my casual go to shoe.","title":"Very comfortable, very predictable fit","username":"Walter"}]

[{"date":"2013-11-19T00:00:00Z","dateAdded":"2015-08-14T18:21:07Z","dateSeen":["2015-08-14T00:00:00Z"],"rating":4.0,"sourceURLs":["http://www.shoes.com/mens-chippewa-29321-12-inch-round-toe-pull-on-briar-pitstop-leather-p2_id325198"],"text":"I kept these boots for a couple of weeks and periodically tried them on. I finally sent them back because the foot leather is stiff and they are heavy. Also. the large heel, which should add stability on rough ground, has a square edge that makes walking cumbersome. (It would take a while to wear a rounded edge and I didn't want that job.) However, the inner sole was comfortable when standing and the thick outer soles would provide support on rough ground. If someone does not mind the weight and is willing to break-in the stiff leather this boot would probably be a good choice for rough, outside work. I am sure they would be durable and they have rugged good looks.","title":"Sturdy and Heavy","username":"Montana 507"}]
